==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Simmer
<hw>Sim"mer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Simmered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Simmering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Prov. E. also
<ets>simper</ets>; -- an onomatopoetic word.]</ety> <def>To boil gently,
or with a gentle hissing; to begin to boil.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I <qex>simmer</qex> as liquor doth on the fire before it beginneth
to boil.</q> <rj><qau>Palsgrave.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Simmer</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Simmer
<hw>Sim"mer</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To cause to boil gently; to cook
in liquid heated almost or just to the boiling point.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Simnel</ent>⟦br⟧
